post_text:
Today, Thursday, July 2, 2020, Governor DeWine announced back to school health and safety guidelines for all school districts across Ohio. Big Walnut Local Schools is currently reviewing those guidelines.

Our school district has been planning and preparing for multiple scenarios to safely welcome students and staff back.

We will be reviewing the latest information from the governor so we can meet the requirements set forth in these guidelines. Once we know more, we will share more details. #InspireAndGuide

post_text: As you may have encountered this morning, Schoology has been intermittently shutting down. Due to many districts beginning remote learning today, the system is overloaded. To put it in perspective, last Monday the site had around 250,000 active users, and this morning, it had over 2 million. We have spoken directly with Schoology leadership and they have their entire engineering team working on the issue as we speak. We will keep you updated when the issue has been resolved. Thank you for your patience and flexibility as we all try to navigate these new obstacles together. #InspireAndGuide

These students and teachers are INSPIRING! Last week, Mrs. Kuzevski and Mrs. Kavalieros' 3rd grade classes at Big Walnut Elementary teamed up to send 40 "Love Boxes" to The Inn at Walnut Trail, a new nursing home in town. They also created 12 dementia fidget blankets for the memory care unit.

Students packed the boxes to include: a pair of socks, an emery board, a deck of cards, chapstick, chocolates, candies, a coloring book and a framed quote or artwork created by the student, markers/crayons and tissues. They also decorated the boxes with a lot of â¤ï¸!

A special thanks to a grant from the Kids Inspiring Kindness Campaign, as well as parents for making this project possible! #InspireAndGuide.

post_text:
This is an autocall that we are sending to families:
Good Afternoon Big Walnut Families, this is Angie Hamberg, your superintendent. I am calling to inform you of an issue within the area. At this time, we are just taking proper safety precautions at each of our buildings, due to a person being pursued by law enforcement. There is no indication that this person poses a threat to any of our buildings, but we are keeping all students inside as a precaution. We know very few details except that the person is on foot and was in the Vans Valley Road area. For parents of half-day kindergarten or preschool students, please provide supervision for your students being dropped off or picked up today. We will provide an update when we know more information.

post_text:
We are excited to feature Cailyn Sutliff, who is one of our kindergarten teachers at General Rosecrans Elementary (GRE)! Cailyn recently joined the kindergarten team after being a reading tutor at GRE. Keep reading to learn more about Cailyn.

â€œHello! My name is Cailyn Sutliff and I am on the kindergarten team at General Rosecrans Elementary. I grew up in Granville, Ohio and now live in New Albany with my husband, Nick. We are both teachers, and love to travel and explore our national parks! I graduated from Ohio State University in December of 2018, and soon after became a reading tutor at GRE. Over the summer, I had the opportunity to join the kindergarten team and have loved every minute of it! To me, #InspireandGuide means providing my students the tools to be successful problem solvers. I want to teach my kids to ask questions and help them become lifelong learners!â€

Thank you, Cailyn! #InspireAndGuide

DID YOU KNOW? The BWHS Print Service team is raising funds in 2019 to help purchase new equipment. This student run services department provides students the experience of running a small business, managing finances, designing/editing art and providing customers in the community with first class work. They have become a trusted leader in the large format printing (e.g. large wall wraps, large-scale prints, and creative design) since it started in 2016.
